# API Layer Rules

## Structure

- One domain per file: `auth.ts`, `bookings.ts`, `services.ts`, `loyalty.ts`, `users.ts`
- Re-export all public functions from `lib/api/index.ts`
- Use `apiClient` from `./client` — do not create new Axios instances

## Adding Endpoints

```typescript
// lib/api/bookings.ts
export async function getBookingDetail(id: string): Promise<BookingDetail> {
  const { data } = await apiClient.get<BookingDetail>(`/bookings/${id}`)
  return data
}
```

## Response Shapes

BE often returns flat `{ success, token, message }` — not always `{ data: T }`. Match existing functions in the same file.

## Auth Tokens

- Access token: `tokenStorage.setAccess()` → localStorage + cookie `aw_access_token`
- Role: `tokenStorage.setRole()` → cookie `aw_role`
- Refresh: httpOnly cookie, auto-handled by response interceptor on 401

## Swagger Is Truth

When contract docs disagree with code, check `http://localhost:5255/swagger` and update `docs/BE_INTEGRATION_NOTES.md` if BE changed.
